cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper focuses on computer-aided diagnosis tools in retinal image analysis, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves modeling the relative geometry and appearance of the Optic disc and Fovea, which requires machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of image retrieval techniques (cs.IR) and the evaluation of results using metrics such as accuracy and F1 score (cs.MM).
